body:
I have the following code:

```
// file `test.sv`

module test;

  initial
    do_stuff();


  function automatic do_stuff();
    int f = $fopen("some_file", "w");
  endfunction

endmodule
```

I'm compiling it with `verilator --binary test.sv` and getting:

```
%Error: test.sv:8:13: syntax error, unexpected $fopen, expecting TYPE-IDENTIFIER
    8 |     int f = $fopen("some_file", "w");
      |             ^~~~~~
%Error: Exiting due to 1 error(s)
```

The code is legal and it works in commercial tools.
